      • substituteElementToRename

        public PsiElement substituteElementToRename(PsiElement element,
                                            Editor editor)
        Returns the element to be renamed instead of the element on which the rename refactoring was invoked (for example, a super method of an inherited method).
        Parameters:
        element - the element on which the refactoring was invoked.
        editor - the editor in which the refactoring was invoked.
        Returns:
        the element to rename, or null if the rename refactoring should be canceled.

      • substituteElementToRename

        public void substituteElementToRename(PsiElement element,
                                      Editor editor,
                                      Pass<PsiElement> renameCallback)
        Substitutes element to be renamed and initiate rename procedure. Should be used in order to prevent modal dialogs to appear during inplace rename
        Parameters:
        element - the element on which refactoring was invoked
        editor - the editor in which inplace refactoring was invoked
        renameCallback - rename procedure which should be called on the chosen substitution
